  "prompt": "Is it a felony to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, in the United States and many other countries, money laundering is a felony.\n\n*   **United States:** Money laundering is a federal crime under 18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1956 and 18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1957. Penalties can include substantial fines (often hundreds of thousands of dollars or more) and lengthy prison sentences, often up to 20 years per violation. The specific penalties depend on the amount of money laundered, the circumstances of the offense, and the specific laws violated.\n\n*   **Other Countries:** Most countries have laws against money laundering, and it's usually considered a serious crime. The penalties can vary, but often include imprisonment, fines, and asset forfeiture.\n\nIt is important to note that the specific laws and penalties can vary depending on the jurisdiction.\n",
